body.name: VASAGLE LED Bed Frame Queen Size, Storage Headboard and Charging Station, Queen Bed Frame with 2 AC Outlets, 1 USB Port, 1 Type-C Port, No Box Spring Needed, Ink Black and Rustic Brown URMB841B01
features: [Storage Headboard with Charging Station] With 1 open shelf, 1 open and 1 hidden compartment, this headboard offers ample room for decor and items you want to keep nearby. Its 2 outlets, along with 1 USB and 1 Type-C port, allow for easy charging

[Color and Mode-Adjustable LED Lights] The LED lights built into the headboard boast 25 colors, 6 brightness levels, 3 flashing modes, and 6 flashing speeds. You can use the remote control to adjust the color and mode to create different atmospheres

[Comfy and Chic] Along with rustic brown panels, a headboard upholstered with black PU means this stylish bed frame will easily blend with any home décor. An ergonomic 105° tilt, meanwhile, makes the headboard comfortable to recline on while reading in bed

[Sturdy Construction, Reliable Support] Made with quality particleboard and supported by sturdy steel slats, this queen-size LED bed frame is robust enough to support up to 1000 lb, giving you peace of mind that you'll enjoy quality rest year after year

[Handy Under-Bed Storage] Keep your bedroom tidy with this bed frame. Its 4.4" distance from the ground allows for easy cleaning and provides ample under-bed space for you to neatly organize clothing, shoes, or extra bedding with storage organizers

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great build quality
reviews.reviewText: I was shocked at the quality of the bed frame for the price. You can tell quality materials are used. It’s real wood, heavy, sturdy, and feels like it will last. It was a bit difficult and time consuming to put together, but nothing worse than some IKEA furniture I have put together, not that IKEA is a very high bar! I would highly recommend having someone help you put this together but it can be done with one person, just set aside a few hours, because it will take a bit. Instructions were pretty clear for the most part. I’m satisfied with the purchase and my son loves it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Solid bed frame!
reviews.reviewText: Great bed frame, sturdy, good height (not for under bed storage), great features & build quality. But it’s not completely silent!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit. Lots of storage. Very Functional for small space
reviews.reviewText: Lots of parts. But reasonably easy to understand directions, with very descriptive pictures. Make sure to review all directions before you attempt assembly. This full sized bed is just perfect for our teenage son, and his tiny little room. He previously had a wooden slatted bed. Over time the slats weren't holding up. This sturdy metal frame will be soooo much better for him. After assembly, My daughter, (who has a queen) and husband (California King) both want a bed like this. And I must admit, I'm a bit jealous of my sons new bed myself. Lol. We may be making additional purchases very soon!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All around great platform bed with headboard you can lean on!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This bed took about an hour to assemble, it is sturdy and solid. Directions are on point and it comes with tools to put it together. Two small flaws: one screw fitting was off due to a welded washer being off a bit, and the outlet should either be screwed on prior to constructing the headboard or a very short screwdriver is needed. Overall I love the look, the lighting is great, the storage area is handy, and the headboard is nice for leaning on. I am glad I chose this one!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Wouldn’t recommend for smaller rooms
reviews.reviewText: The bed frame is sturdy but it took me ages to put it together and I'm usually really good at these types of things. If you have a temper and you’re easily frustrated please be sure to have someone help you. ESPECIALLY with the storage door. My outlet that came with the bed doesn’t work but it’s not a huge deal to me. There was a couple holes that were missing for the screws but I was able to drill them myself. My room is kind of small so I have kicked the corner of this frame sever times in the last three days, so be aware of that. I like it okay but nothing to be super excited over.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Slats: perfect.Rails: Minor issue with a simple fix. I had to fold and cut part of a paper towel so that three ends of the rail would fit flushed.Headboard: It's good.Texture: perfectBuilding Process: I definitely needed a drill. The second step before the last step would be difficult for one person to follow. The joint (what makes the headboard opens) would have to be put on the side of the headboard first so that it's easier to add the last piece. No screws lost, extra screws is there if needed. Overall it felt good putting together and seeing it light up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bed, LED not built to last (update)
reviews.reviewText: The bed was easy and only took about 2 hours to build. The bed frame itself is good and sturdy. However , beware of the LED bar on the bed. It went out after minimal use after only having the bed for 2 weeks. If that’s not something you care about, then the bed is a 10/10. I care though. 4/10Update!! : so it turns out if you have more than two cords in the little outlets, the lights won’t turn on . No idea it did that but I’m reprimanding my review. It’s working and great . 10/10
